The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Radical quits Assembly

 Islamabad, July 14 (PTI): The chief of Pakistans Opposition party, Jamat-e-Islami, Qazi Hussain Ahmed, today resigned from the National assembly in protest against the military operation on the Lal Masjid.

 Ahmed, who is also the president of the Muthahida Majlis-e-Amal, said: I am announcing my resignation from the National Assembly and will move the supreme court against the killing of innocent religious students in the military operation. 

 General Musharraf has committed a cruel act to please the Americans, he said here today. 




